Please don't Close this issue. I have investigated many days.

In [JwtBearerHandler](https://github.com/dotnet/aspnetcore/blob/b41e166aac4746253b541ce512eaeff8dbf73112/src/Security/Authentication/JwtBearer/src/JwtBearerHandler.cs#L84) the scheme is being hard-coded as a string literal rather than using the scheme that was defined in its configuration. 

The `Scheme` property is available on the base class https://github.com/dotnet/aspnetcore/blob/b41e166aac4746253b541ce512eaeff8dbf73112/src/Security/Authentication/Core/src/AuthenticationHandler.cs#L23C12-L23C40

I think it would make sense to use the `Scheme` property here instead of hard-coding "Bearer" - otherwise you can't define authentication like this:

```csharp
builder.Services.AddAuthentication(JwtBearerDefaults.AuthenticationScheme)
.AddJwtBearer(JwtBearerDefaults.AuthenticationScheme, cfg =>
{
    cfg.Audience = options.Audience;
    cfg.Authority = options.Authority;

    if (options.MetadataAddress is not null)
        cfg.MetadataAddress = options.MetadataAddress;

    cfg.RequireHttpsMetadata = options.RequireHttpsMetadata;

    cfg.TokenValidationParameters = new TokenValidationParameters
    {
        NameClaimType = "sub",
        RoleClaimType = ClaimTypes.Role,
        ValidateAudience = true,
        ValidateIssuer = true,
        ValidIssuer = options.Authority,
        ClockSkew = TimeSpan.FromSeconds(5),
        ValidAudience = options.Audience
    };
})
// In my use-case, this second scheme is used by my Blazor app to get the current user
// during token construction (in an `IClaimsTransformation` so that custom, app specific 
// roles and permissions can be added to the token to be used with `[Authorize(Roles = "")]`
// in my Blazor components.
.AddJwtBearer("Service", cfg =>
{
    var key = new SymmetricSecurityKey(Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes("my-key"));
    cfg.TokenValidationParameters = new TokenValidationParameters
    {
        NameClaimType = ClaimTypes.NameIdentifier,
        RoleClaimType = ClaimTypes.Role,
        
        IssuerSigningKey = key,
        ValidateIssuer = true,
        ValidIssuer = "MyCustomIssuer",
        ValidateAudience = true,
        ValidAudience = "https://TemplateProject.api",
        ClockSkew = TimeSpan.FromSeconds(5)
    };
});
```

