### Describe the bug

`RequestDelegateGenerator` in a project targetting `net9.0` generates invalid code for array parameters.

The generator tries to assign single parsed value to an array parameter.

Snipped from the generated code
```csharp
global::System.Int32[]? ids_local = new global::System.Int32[ids_temp.Length];
for (var i = 0; i < ids_temp.Length; i++)
{
    var element = ids_temp[i];
    global::System.Int32[]? parsed_element = default;
    if (GeneratedRouteBuilderExtensionsCore.TryParseExplicit<int>(element!, CultureInfo.InvariantCulture, out var element_parsed_non_nullable))
    {
        parsed_element = element_parsed_non_nullable; // THIS LINE IS NOT VALID, element_parse_non_nullable is int, not an int[]
    }
    else if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(element))
    {
        parsed_element = default;
    }
    else
    {
        wasParamCheckFailure = true;
    }
    ids_local[i] = parsed_element!;
}
```

I think the issue is at this [line](https://github.com/dotnet/aspnetcore/blob/b41e166aac4746253b541ce512eaeff8dbf73112/src/Http/Http.Extensions/gen/StaticRouteHandlerModel/EndpointParameter.cs#L382), where instead of `typeSymbol`, there should be a `parameterType` variable written into the output.


